plores the complexity of Hodgson’s thought, the daring of his ideas, and the global context of his world historical insights into, among other themes, Islam and world history, gender in Islam, and the problem of Muslim universality. In our post-9/11 world, Hodgson’s historical vision and moral engagement have never been more relevant. A towering achievement, Islam and World History will prove to be the definitive statement on Hodgson’s relevance in the twenty-first century and will introduce his influential work to a new generation of readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHodgson, Marshall G. S. 0aIslamic countries-History. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aHodgson.  aIslam.  aOrientalism.  agender.  atradition.  auniversality.  aworld history.1 aBayly, Christopher A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Edmund, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Edmund, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCheddadi, Abdesselam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrossley, Pamela Kyle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDakhlia, Jocelyne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevji, Faisal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeyer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMankin, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMankin, Robert J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNaumann, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.deg